    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nVertical conceal extmarks can be not updated if lines are set when built-in completion menu (`:h ins-completion-menu`) is shown.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create the following 'init.lua':\n\n    ```lua\n    -- Prepare a buffer with attached 'markdown' tree-sitter parser\n    local buf_id = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\n    vim.api.nvim_set_current_buf(buf_id)\n    vim.treesitter.start(buf_id, 'markdown')\n    vim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(buf_id, 0, -1, false, { '```lua', 'local a = 1', '```' })\n\n    -- Show it in a split. Use maximum conceal for demo purposes (reproduces without it)\n    vim.wo.conceallevel = 3\n    vim.cmd('vsplit | enew')\n\n    local change_lines = function()\n      -- IMPORTANT: start showing Pmenu BEFORE changing lines\n      vim.fn.complete(1, { 'Hello', 'World' })\n\n      -- Set new lines in the markdown buffer\n      vim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(buf_id, 0, -1, false, { 'Invisible!' })\n\n      -- Collect information about conceal extmarks for demo purpose\n      vim.defer_fn(function()\n        local ts_ns_id = vim.api.nvim_get_namespaces()['nvim.treesitter.highlighter']\n        _G.marks = vim.api.nvim_buf_get_extmarks(buf_id, ts_ns_id, 0, -1, { details = true })\n      end, 10)\n    end\n    vim.keymap.set('i', '<M-m>', change_lines)\n    ```\n2. `nvim --clean -u init.lua`\n3. Press `i` to start Insert mode and press `<M-m>`. The text in the right split disappears.\n4. Type `:=marks` which should show that markdown buffer still had vertical conceal extmarks.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nConceal extmarks are always up to date.\nI bisected this directly to the 8ba047e33fe3a10765c593c810d54b5e3bb906e9 (i.e. #31324, cc @luukvbaal).\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-89+g57d99a515f\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, doesn't have this functionality\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64, 6.13.8-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.1.3-arch1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage and from source",
